rComments: Not a professor who should be teaching a course to hundreds of first years. All over the place, unclear, hard to understand and does not care about helping students like other professors. uOttawa is plagued with poor-mediocre math profs and this is one I would avoid if possible.

She was an okay prof but not very interactive. She literally walked in, said her name and class code then started the lesson. She is nice but can be boring. Overall, it was a decent class and her lack of teaching experience  is made up for with clear criteria and helpful DGDs. The textbook was also good for extra practice but not 100% needed.

She was okay but very reserved and didn't interact with students. 2 assignments, 2 midterms and a cumulative final. They were all fair and she even knocked marks off of the total to help us out. If you're bad at math I wouldn't recommend because she wasn't always clear(french accent) but she was nice and fair. I'd take another class with her again.

She is a new prof and wasn't the best at explaining the concepts. Thick French accent so it was sometimes hard to understand her English. The DGD was really helpful. Tests and exam aren't hard if you take good notes and study what was taught in the DGD.

Textbook never used .. though it does simplify solutions .. only 2 small assignments. completely understand the DGDs and answer in the same sequence she does on the DGD and you have a chance on getting an A+ ... shes easy through out the session. but beware of the final it will lower your mark
